tions of some of his major pieces as well as works that have never been published in English. The collection brings Lotman into the orbit of contemporary concerns such as gender, memory, performance, world literature, and urban life. It is aimed at students from various disciplines and is augmented by an introduction and notes that elucidate the relevant contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCulturexSemiotic models. 0aSemiotics. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aCultural commentary.  aEstonia.  aPetersburg.  aPushkin.  aRussia.  aSoviet Union.  aaesthetics.  aarchitecture.  aaristocracy.  aart.  aartificial intelligence.  acities.  aclass.  acomparative literature.  acriticism.  adrama.  afeminism.  agender.  aintellectual history.  alandscape design.  amemory.  anobility.  apainting.  aperformance.  apoetry.  apost-structuralism.  asemiotics.  asocial critique.  astructure.  atheater.  atheory.  atwentieth century.  aurban studies.  awomen.1 aPaloff, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaloff, Benjamin.1 aSchönle, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchönle, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook